WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.320
I'm going to talk to you today about, I decided to start more broad because I realized that

00:00:06.320 --> 00:00:10.640
the audience is between lymphoma, myeloma, and leukemia.

00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:15.220
So I'm going to talk to you about why we're excited about the combination of BCL-2 and

00:00:15.220 --> 00:00:18.560
menin inhibition, and then I'll take you through some of the zyftominib data.

00:00:19.340 --> 00:00:23.320
So first, the mechanism of action of menin inhibitors.

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:27.960
So menin inhibitors are the latest targeted therapies approved for acute myeloid leukemia.

00:00:28.380 --> 00:00:33.540
They are approved for these indications, KMT-2A rearranged leukemias, which used to be called

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:39.500
MLL, mixed lineage leukemia, which happened in about 5% to 10% of acute leukemia, and

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.600
MPM-1 mutant acute leukemia, 25% to 30% of AML.

00:00:43.020 --> 00:00:48.680
The common thing about both of these genotypes is upregulation of HOX genes, which are normally

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:52.900
stem cell programmed, so they're hijacked because of this HOX upregulation that leads

00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:58.360
to differentiation and arrest, and menin inhibitors create a wedge between menin and KMT-2A,

00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:03.420
these two proteins, that causes downregulation of HOX genes and an anti-leukemic effect.

00:01:04.620 --> 00:01:08.320
So there are two menin inhibitors approved, revuminib and zyftominib.

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:12.860
There are multiple menin inhibitors right now in clinical investigation, and these are

00:01:12.860 --> 00:01:15.520
the structures of these menin inhibitors.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:21.900
So you can think of them as medicines similar to revuminib or medicines similar to zyftominib.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:25.040
The circled part is the part that binds to the menin pocket.

00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:33.400
And there are now even second-generation menin inhibitors entering the clinic, with AstraZeneca's

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:36.640
trial launched and the CHARM study about to launch.

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:42.940
And this is because there's robust data showing that these menin inhibitors work.

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:48.980
So revuminib is approved for both KMT-2A and MPM-1 for relapsed refractory acute leukemia

00:01:48.980 --> 00:01:54.480
age 1 and above, and zyftominib is approved for NPM-1 relapsed and refractory acute myeloid

00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:54.900
leukemia.

00:01:55.140 --> 00:02:01.320
And the reason why we got approval is because these medicines improved on the historical

00:02:01.320 --> 00:02:03.220
outcomes in these genotypes.

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:09.100
So if you look at KMT-2A rearranged leukemias, especially if they've had two or more lines

00:02:09.100 --> 00:02:14.320
of therapy, their median overall survival is less than a few months.

00:02:15.560 --> 00:02:19.460
Whereas for NPM-1, for first salvage, the outcomes are reasonable.

00:02:19.940 --> 00:02:23.840
They're not favorable, but they're just like any other relapsed refractory leukemia.

00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:24.020
And then for MPM-1, they're just like any other relapsed refractory leukemia.

00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:24.080
And then for MPM-1, they're just like any other relapsed refractory leukemia.

00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:24.180
And then for MPM-1, they're just like any other relapsed refractory leukemia.

00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:24.240
And then for MPM-1, they're just like any other relapsed refractory leukemia.

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:27.560
And then for later salvage lines, it is worse.

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:34.160
So MENIN inhibitors lead to a CR-CRH rate of roughly 20% to 30%, but the duration of response

00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:37.800
in this and relapsed refractory disease is limited to about six months.

00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:40.360
And that's mostly because of these mutations.

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:44.580
The best described mechanism of resistance is these MEN1 mutations.

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:49.660
These are binding site mutation of these inhibitors that disrupt the binding of MENIN.

00:02:50.340 --> 00:02:53.340
And in this case, or sorry, disrupt the binding of the drug.

00:02:53.460 --> 00:02:54.220
Do not disrupt the binding.

00:02:54.220 --> 00:03:00.980
And there could be a specific set of mutations for each of these MEN1 inhibitors that would affect

00:03:00.980 --> 00:03:03.640
the choice of MEN1 inhibitors in the future.

00:03:03.940 --> 00:03:08.380
So just like CML, you may imagine one day a heat map where you have a mutation,

00:03:08.560 --> 00:03:12.800
and you're going to say, this one works better for zoftominib versus revumenib, et cetera.

00:03:14.260 --> 00:03:20.360
So aside from being practical of combining BCL2 inhibition and MEN1 inhibition,

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:22.940
because Benetoclax is a standard of care,

00:03:23.260 --> 00:03:24.200
there's excellent science that says that if you have a MEN1 inhibitor,

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:25.880
there's good science to support this combination.

00:03:26.380 --> 00:03:35.040
The basis for it is from these early studies showing that a BCL2 inhibitor targets more the stem-like cells in leukemia,

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:41.080
whereas a MEN1 inhibitor would target more the common myeloprogenitor-like phenotype.

00:03:41.420 --> 00:03:47.320
And then the combination would eradicate leukemia, both, you know, progenitor and stem cells.

00:03:47.480 --> 00:03:50.860
And that would lead to prolonged survival in these animal models.

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:54.180
In addition, there's more recent studies showing that MEN1 inhibition,

00:03:54.180 --> 00:03:58.300
in fact, down-regulates BCL2 expression and MCL1 expression.

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:03.220
So that could induce sensitivity to BCL2 inhibition.

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:07.800
So that's the basis of multiple clinical trials that have shown these results.

00:04:08.760 --> 00:04:12.160
Our IST at MD Anderson is safe, but there are also investigator,

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:16.560
there are also company-sponsored studies, such as the ACE of N-zoftominib.

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:18.860
There's Frontline, there's Rehabs Refractory.

00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:24.080
I will just use the first two studies to pinpoint the importance of MEN1 and BCL2,

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:26.520
and I'll give you a little bit more detail on that as we go along.

00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:28.660
And I'll give you a little bit more detail on that as we go along.

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:32.360
So, for example, FA-revuminib led to far less response compared to the studies with BCL2 and MEN1.

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:35.860
And that is probably because all these patients were exposed to cytarabine,

00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:40.700
and the magnitude of the effect seen with FA-revuminib is mostly the revuminib,

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:45.900
and less the chemotherapy, whereas BCL2 and MEN1 inhibition seems to be synergistic.

00:04:46.440 --> 00:04:53.800
So, the COMET-007 is a large study that investigated either 7+3+-zoftominib as a phase 1,

00:04:53.800 --> 00:04:54.140
or 8-7+-zoftominib as a phase 1.

00:04:54.140 --> 00:05:00.900
There was a relapsed refractory population, and then a newly diagnosed population.

00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:05.780
And we presented these data at ASH about the relapsed refractory population.

00:05:05.780 --> 00:05:11.000
So, it included NPM1 mutant patients, 51 patients, and KMT2A rearranged patients.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:14.780
And the bulk of the study in here that we're going to present is focused

00:05:14.780 --> 00:05:18.020
on the NPM1 mutant population.

00:05:18.020 --> 00:05:24.120
So, the recommended phase 2 dose of zoftominib is 600 milligrams daily.

00:05:24.120 --> 00:05:29.700
And these are patients that were heavily pretreated, about 51% had prior venetoclax,

00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:32.360
about 20% had prior transplant.

00:05:33.300 --> 00:05:38.460
And what we saw is, you know, side effects that are things we expect

00:05:38.460 --> 00:05:43.280
with an HMA/VEN combination relapsed refractory setting without excessive toxicity.

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:47.940
So, there was no clear increase in myelosuppression with zoftominib.

00:05:47.940 --> 00:05:50.640
There was acceptable count recovery.

00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:54.100
There is -- there wasn't a high --

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:56.080
a rate of QT prolongation.

00:05:56.420 --> 00:05:59.980
And like what we saw with other targeted agents, there was lower rate

00:05:59.980 --> 00:06:03.780
of differentiation syndrome, which is the main class effect of these drugs.

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:07.240
So, when used in combination, there's less expected differentiation syndrome.

00:06:07.240 --> 00:06:12.500
So, the overall response rate with HMA/VEN and zoftominib was 65%.

00:06:12.500 --> 00:06:17.500
The CR rate was 27% with an excellent MRD negativity rate.

00:06:17.500 --> 00:06:20.480
And this was done by flow, but also we did some analysis

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:24.080
by in vivo scribe showing high rates of MRD negativity.

00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:29.020
Impressively, the overall survival in this relapsed refractory cohort was great.

00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:35.940
For someone -- for an NPM1 refractory cohort, a median duration of CRC was 39 weeks.

00:06:35.940 --> 00:06:39.400
So, this is excellent, especially for those who are VEN naive.

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:42.720
There's less of a benefit, probably, for those that are VEN exposed.

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:50.060
So, in conclusion, I hope that I showed you preclinical studies showing strong support

00:06:50.280 --> 00:06:54.060
or synergy between BCL2 and menin inhibition across --

00:06:54.060 --> 00:06:59.820
multiple trials, the combination of the menin inhibitor zoftominib at the RP2D,

00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:05.040
which is 600 milligrams with VEN and EZA, is well-tolerated and is showing deep

00:07:05.040 --> 00:07:10.500
and durable remissions in patients with relapsed refractory NPM1 mutant acute myeloid leukemia.

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:14.020
And there are -- based on these results, based on the results

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:16.640
of multiple trials incorporating menin inhibitors,

00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:22.700
there are multiple pivotal randomized studies launched testing the addition of menin inhibition

00:07:22.700 --> 00:07:24.040
to either EZA or VEN.

00:07:24.040 --> 00:07:30.140
And I'm going to talk to you in another session about design of these trials.

00:07:30.140 --> 00:07:31.100
Thank you.
